<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>ASL's contents tagged with "conexões globais 2.0"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/asl</link><description>ASL's contents tagged with "conexões globais 2.0"</description><item><title>Conexões Globais 2.0 to discuss new ways of social mobilization over the web</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0039/7641/conexoes-imagens.jpg" height="200" alt="" style="float: left; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 6px; margin-right: 6px;" width="250"&gt;Associação Software Livre.Org and the State Government from Rio Grande do Sul organized the event Conexões Globais 2.0 (Global Connexions 2.0). The event, that happens together with the Social Forum, 25 to 28 January, at the Casa de Cultura Mario Quintana will harbor important discussions about new technologies, digital culture and social mobilization. To accomplish that, activists and international specialists will be present or will participate in panels remotely from their countries.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The programme includes talks, webconferences (with activists who experienced mobilizations in other parts of the world) about subjects like social media, sustainability, rights in the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Internet and democracy 2.0. Workshops and deconferences will also be carried on. Another hot topic for the event is the cultural programme. With live broadcast via Internet, all the communication of the Conexões Globais 2.0 will be collaborative, produced by its own participants.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Software Livre Radio will broadcast debates and interviews right from the location during the days of the event.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;See the &lt;a href="http://conexoesglobais.com.br/"&gt;event's website&lt;/a&gt; and the programme and participate!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Feb 2012 00:06:23 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/asl/noticias/conexoes-globais-2.0-to-discuss-new-ways-of-social-mobilization-over-the-web</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/asl/noticias/conexoes-globais-2.0-to-discuss-new-ways-of-social-mobilization-over-the-web</guid></item><item><title>Conexões Globais 2.0 discute novas possibilidades de mobilização social pela web</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0039/7641/conexoes-imagens.jpg" height="200" alt="" style="border-color: initial; float: left; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 6px; margin-right: 6px;" width="250"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;A Associação Software Livre.Org juntamente com o Governo do &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: small;"&gt;Estado do RS realizam em Porto Alegre o Conexões Globais 2.0. O evento, que acontece em paralelo ao Fórum Social Temático, de 25 a 28 de janeiro, na Casa de Cultura Mário Quintana promoverá importantes discussões sobre novas tecnologias, cultura digital e mobilização social. Para isso, grandes ativistas e especialistas internacionais estarão presentes ou participarão de paines diretamente de seus países.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;A programação inclui diálogos e webconferências (com ativistas que participaram de mobilizações em outras partes do mundo) sobre temas como mídias sociais, sustentabilidade, direitos na internet e democracia 2.0. Também serão realizadas oficinas e desconferências. Outro destaque do evento é a programação cultural.  Com transmissão AO VIVO via internet, toda a comunicação do Conexões Globais 2.0 será colaborativa, ou seja, produzida pelos próprios participantes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;A Rádio Software Livre transmitirá debates e entrevistas direto da CCMQ durante os dias do evento.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Acesse o &lt;a href="http://conexoesglobais.com.br/"&gt;site do evento&lt;/a&gt;, conheça a programação e participe!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
